WHO   — The Cabazon Dinosaurs — the roadside shrine
WHAT  — The shrine at the end of the pilgrimage: a real roadside attraction that becomes the altar where Jimmy sets his grief down.
WHERE — WIZ · The Wizard (1989)  Framework inputs: The Wizard (1989, dir. Todd Holland, Universal); verified cast & Nintendo history  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the grief needed a place to be laid down, and the film found a real, absurd, perfect monument for it.
HOW   — By being exactly the kind of strange, larger-than-life place a child decides is where you say goodbye.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  A tourist-trap dinosaur, turned into the spot where a boy finally lets his sister go.

